Question: How can I create a list of all the files in a directory in Java?
Please using this api: Files.list.
Answer:<<<api>>>: Files.list
<<<code>>>: 
Path path = Paths.get("directoryPath");
List<String> files = new ArrayList<>();
Files.list(path)
    .filter(Files::isRegularFile)
    .forEach(file -> files.add(file.getFileName().toString()));
<<<explanation>>>: The Files.list() method returns a Stream of Path objects representing the files in the directory. The filter() method is used to only include regular files in the stream. The forEach() method is used to add each file name to the list.
